  <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_tod_1818_rasgbi_tod170_34.jpg"/>
         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="eng" type="laterAddition" rend="top centre">
            <p>Art. 34<gap/></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="raj" type="invocation" rend="top centre">
            <p>श्री ऋष्नायनमः श्रीरामजी</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div2" corresp="#orig_div2">
            <p>Bow to Shri <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_krishna">Krishna</ref><note>This invocation is in Sanskrit.</note> Shri <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_ram">Ram</ref> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="raj" type="laterAddition" rend="top centre">
            <p><placeName ref="#devgarh">देवगढ</placeName> रा रावत <persName ref="#gokulDas">गोकल दास</persName> जी रा परवाना री नकल
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div3" corresp="#orig_div3">
            <p>Copy of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_parvana">parvana</ref> of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rawat">Rawat</ref> <persName ref="#gokulDas">Gokul Das</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref> of <placeName ref="#devgarh">Devgarh</placeName><note>This is a clerical note from the scribe who copied the document.</note></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div4" xml:lang="raj" type="authorisation" rend="top centre">
            <p>सही</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div4" corresp="#orig_div4">
            <p>Certified</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div5" xml:lang="raj" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>सिध श्री माहारावत जी श्री <persName ref="#gokulDas">गोकलदास</persName> जी बचनात च्यारी मसल रा पटाय-
               <lb/>तां दसे सो प्रसाद बांचजो अप्रंच बिना खून कणी पटायत रो चडस गांम ऊ-
               <lb/>तारणो नही अर तगसीर मै प‌ड़ ही जावै तो च्यारी मसल रा भाया नें पूछे नै ओ-
               <lb/>लंभो दैणो न्ही बिना पूछ्यां ओलंभो देंवा तो म्हानै श्री नाथ जी री सोगन छै अ-
               <lb/>णी मै तफावत पडै न्ही <date calendar="#samvat-chaitradi"><choice><abbr>सं</abbr><expan>संवत</expan></choice> १८७४ पोस बद ६</date>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div5" corresp="#orig_div5">
            <p>
               <lb/>Success! By the order of Shri <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_maharawat">Maharawat</ref> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref> Shri <persName ref="#gokulDas">Gokul Das</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_jiu">Ji</ref>, proclaim benevolent
               <lb/>greetings to the four ranks of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pattayat">pattayats</ref>. Thereafter: [ordered that] without fault,<note>The word 'khun' most commonly means blood but is also used in Rajasthani in the sense of crime, offense or sin.</note> 
               a <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pattayat">pattayat's</ref> <unclear>traditional</unclear><note>This may be a technical revenue term. The term 'charas' most commonly is used to refer either a resin extracted from hemp or the leather buckets used to carry water in a Persian wheel, in Rajasthani it can also mean 'traditional,' which seems more likely here.</note> village [rights] 
               <lb/>shall not be withdrawn. And if he should commit an offense, then he shall make an inquiry from the brotherhood of the four ranks and
               <lb/>a reprimand shall not be made [by <persName ref="#gokulDas">Gokul Das</persName>]. If we give a reprimand without an inquiry, then we take the oath of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_shrinathji">Shrinathji</ref>.
               <lb/>In this [matter], there shall be no disparity. <date calendar="#samvat-chaitradi">Samvat [Year] 1874 Pausha <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_badi">badi</ref> 6</date>.
            </p>
         </div>
